Description. Female (
Figs. 5 and 6
): Measurements : Approximate body length: 15.0; head width: 4.8 ; forewing length: 11.0; F 1 length: 0.9 ; F 2 length: 0.2 ; F 3 length: 0.3 ; mandible length: 2.3 ; mandible basal width: 1.1 ; thorax width: 6.2 . Coloration: Dark brown (
Figs. 5 and 6
), lighter in legs. Wing membranes light brown with dark brown veins (
Fig. 6
) and bluish iridescence. Integument and sculpture surface: Very shiny, mainly on the metasoma. Clypeus with coarse and dense punctation, denser towards the lower edge (
Fig. 5
) and with an irregular unpunctated longitudinal area on the disc. Labrum with fine, dense and uniform punctation (
Fig. 5
). Terga with very fine and dense punctation, dispersed on the distal half of each tergite and with smooth distal edges. T 2 with denser and finer punctation than that of the other terga. Pubescence: Dark brown with yellowish brown hairs on the lateroanterior surface of the mesoscutum and light brown on the lower edge of the pronotal lobe (
Figs. 5 and 6
). Clypeal disc with short and mostly simple hairs. Labrum with branched and dense pilosity, with long, simple and curved downward hairs intermixed. Terga with short and simple pilosity mixed with some long and branched hairs on T 1 and on the lateral sides of the distal tergites. Prepygidial fimbria slightly semicircular with coarse and mostly simple hairs. Structures: Flabellum elliptic with the anterior edge projected forward. Maxillary palpus with four palpomeres ( 2 nd> 3 rd> 1 st> 4 th). Mandible with five teeth with acute apices (except third with apex slightly truncate) (
Fig. 5
). Trimmal angle acute, poorly developed. Acetabular carina reaching the base of the third tooth (
Fig. 5
). Clypeus strongly convex (lateral view). Labrum semicircular (
Fig. 5
) with flat disc and truncated distal edge. Vertex above the upper ocular tangent (
Fig. 5
). Inner orbits of compound eyes converging below (
Fig. 5
). Distance between the lateral ocellus and the eye more than three times the diameter of the median ocellus (
Fig. 5
). Fore elaiospathe with the secondary anterior comb formed by three giant hairs. Hind elaiospathe with the hairs of the primary anterior comb forming a continuous structure. Primary basitibial plate elliptical, smooth and shiny, with secondary plate lanceolate. Claws with preapical tooth poorly developed, mainly in the hind leg.

Male (
Figs. 7 and 8
): Measurements : Approximate body length: 14.1 ; head width: 4.9 ; forewing length: 11.8 ; F 1 length: 0.9 ; F 2 length: 0.2 ; F 3 length: 0.3 ; mandible length: 1.7 ; mandible basal width: 0.9 ; thorax width: 5.8 . Coloration: Dark brown (
Figs. 7 and 8
), lighter on legs and sterna. Flagellum (except F 1 ) light brown, darker on the posterior surface and lighter on F 2 . Wing membranes and veins light brown, without iridescence (
Fig. 8
). Integument and sculpture surface: Very shiny, mainly on the metasoma. Clypeus finely areolate on the center of the disc, with coarse punctation, slightly dispersed on the upper margin (
Fig. 7
). Labrum with fine and dense punctation, denser than of the clypeus (
Fig. 7
). Terga with dense and very fine punctation, slightly more dispersed towards the distal margin of each tergite. T 2 with finer and denser punctures than that of the other terga. Terga with smooth distal margin. Pubescence: Dark brown, except mesoscutum, lateroposterior margin of the mesoscutellum and anterior margin of the tegula with brown yellowish pilosity (
Fig. 8
). Lateral edge of the pronotal lobe with yellowish hairs. Disc of the mesoscutellum with dark brown hairs, slightly darker than the pubescence present in other parts of the body. Terga with short and simple hairs, with some long and branched hairs mixed on T 1 and on the sides of the distal terga. Trochanter of fore leg and ventral surface of the mesosoma with yellowish brown hairs. Distal tarsus of middle leg with a tuft of plumose hairs at the base of the posterior claw. Hind leg with a tuft of plumose hairs at the base of both claws. Structures: Mandible with three teeth with acute apices (
Fig. 7
). Apical tooth larger than the other two which are subequal in size (
Fig. 7
). Second tooth closer to the third than to the apical tooth (
Fig. 7
). Acetabular carina reaching the base of the third tooth (
Fig. 7
). Trimmal angle obtuse, poorly developed. Upper half of the clypeal disc convex and lower half concave (lateral view). Labrum semicircular (
Fig. 7
) with slightly truncated distal margin and slightly concave longitudinally disc. Vertex below the ocular tangent (
Fig. 7
). Inner orbits of compound eyes converging above (
Fig. 7
). Distance between the lateral ocellus and the eye shorter than the diameter of the median ocellus (
Fig. 7
). Hind femur widened. Claws with preapical tooth.
